🫓HEALTHY AREPAS 🫓❤️🇻🇪 
.
For the fact that arepas are a carb, it doesn’t mean that they aren’t healthy & you have to stop eating them.
They actually are healthier than bread 🥖 because their glycemic index is lower and it triggers less Insulin. 

💌 Save and Share with a friend who likes arepas, gorditas o pupusas.

✨INGREDIENTS:
• 1/2 cup Pre-cook white corn (P.A.N)
• 2 tbsp chia seeds
• 1/4 cup oats
• 2 tbsp flax seeds
• 2 cups of water 
• Salt

✨PREPARATION:
In a bowl add all the ingredients, mix well so that there are no lumps. Knead with your hands until you get a smooth and homogeneous dough. 
Preheat a pan, griddle or budare, over medium heat. Grease very lightly.
Divide the dough into a few balls and use your hands to shape the arepas. Cook for about 4-5 min on each side👌🏼

Fill it with nutritious fillings such as eggs, chicken, turkey, avocado, beans…

Wine and greens 🍷🥬

A yum and healthy snack 🥜🍫Recipe is below!

Only 4 ingredients. 

💌 Save and share with someone who loves peanut butter & chocolate

✨INGREDIENTS:
•Bananas
•Melted Dark Chocolate (No sugar added)
•1/4 cup Peanut Butter
•A handful of chopped peanuts 

✨PREPARATION:
-Slice bananas and lay on parchment paper.
-Add about 1/2 teaspoon of peanut butter on each banana slice
-Add another banana slice on top of the peanut butter to complete the sandwich.
-Freeze for about 20-30min.
-Melt chocolate
-Dip bananas in chocolate
-Sprinkle toppings (chopped peanuts or sea salt)
-Return them to the freezer for 30min or until firm. ENJOY!
Store in freezer 🫶🏻

Ideal to take to the beach, park or the office.

INGREDIENTS✨
-4 cups of pasta already cooked (I used protein pasta)
-1/2 a diced Red onion
-2 chopped Carrots (I cooked them before)
-Cup of sliced celery (optional)
-1/2 cup of corn 🌽 
-Chopped cilantro (to your liking)
-1 can of tuna

For the Dressing, Blend:
•3 tbs Greek yogurt
•Cilantro
•2 garlic gloves minced
•juice of 1 lime 🍋
•2 tsp EVOO (Extra Virgen Olive Oil)
•Salt and Black Pepper

Mix all the ingredients and the dressing together 🥣 Enjoy!

Beets N Berries Overnight Oats 🫙🥄🌺

Comenta que otro sabor te gustaría probar😋

✨INGREDIENTES (por frasco)
-1/2 taza de avena en hojuelas
-1 cdita de semillas de chia
- una pizca de canela
-1 cdita de maple syrup 🍁 (también puedes usar miel o estevia para endulzar)
-2 cdas de yogurt griego

Licuar:
-1 taza de fresas
-1/2 taza de remolacha
- media banana 🍌 (opcional)
-1 taza de leche vegetal (yo utilicé de coco🥛🥥)
(Está mezcla es suficiente para 3 porciones)

PREPARACIÓN✨
Agrega la avena, las semillas de chia, canela y maple syrup en un frasco (te recomiendo utilizar frascos con tapa).
Distribuye la mezcla rosada previamente licuada y homogénea en los frascos, Revuelve todo bien y agrega el yogurt griego encima. Lleva a la nevera durante la noche o por mínimo 2 horas. Agrega tus toppings favoritos (frutas, almendras, peanut butter, coco, etc) DISFRUTA💖💕

💌 Guarda y comparte con alguien que le guste el color rosado o #barbie
